The reason value PMs missed stocks like $AMZN a decade ago and $TSLA now is because many don‚Äôt go out more than a year or two in forecasting earnings or cash flow. No growth manager values a company growing volumes at 50%+ CAGR over the next five years on current year earnings.

You can‚Äôt value a growth stock on next year‚Äôs P/E.  Or you would have missed $AMZN, $SQ, $SHOP, and of course $TSLA.  You have to take your full earnings forecast (industry size, share, pricing, margins) out at least 5 years, snd most value guys just aren‚Äôt comfortable with that.
